Dear Hiring Team, 

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the Java Developer position with CGI. I bring over three years of professional experience in full-stack development with Java, React, and Python, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY with a 4.0 GPA.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade systems that directly reflect the technical depth this position demands. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I translated software requirements into scalable, secure platform services, designing 1,000+ API endpoints with rigorous input validation, error handling, and safe execution across a microservices architecture. I developed UI interfaces using React and JavaScript for developer tools including API templates, SDK patterns, and code-generation workflows, directly mirroring the Front End and UI development responsibilities central to this role. I participated in code reviews and Agile development processes, ensuring architectural alignment, adherence to coding standards, and troubleshooting application code-related issues — the exact collaborative engineering discipline this team values. Prior to Sperse, as a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I designed and developed scalable, secure Java-based applications using Spring Boot, React, and AWS, supporting thousands of users across 30+ applications in an Identity & Access Management platform. This work required deep JEE internals expertise in Transaction management and Memory Management, and I collaborated extensively with the QA team using GIT and JIRA to diagnose and fix bugs, write unit and integration tests using Java testing tools, and ensure high-quality code delivery in Agile sprints. Together, these roles have prepared me to contribute meaningfully to CGI's core engineering responsibilities and drive impact within an agile, collaborative team environment.

My academic research experience has given me a rigorous foundation in systems architecture, technical communication, and mentorship — skills that translate directly into the hands-on coaching and support responsibilities central to this role. As an AI Researcher at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I conducted applied research on StyleGAN and Stable Diffusion using Python and PyTorch on Pace University's HPC cluster, implementing model training and fine-tuning workflows with LORA. Beyond building the systems myself, I provided hands-on coaching for 50+ students through workshops on GPU programming and building AI Agents with LangChain, LangGraph, and LangSmith. Designing and delivering those sessions required me to break down complex technical concepts clearly and accessibly, act as a technical advisor on specialized phases of system design and implementation, and lead participants through major development workflows — directly mirroring the mentorship and knowledge-sharing responsibilities this role demands. This experience has shaped me into an engineer who builds with rigor, communicates with clarity, and supports junior team members effectively, all of which I would bring to CGI's team and mission.

I have always been passionate about partnership, quality, and objectivity in delivering IT solutions, and I envision myself contributing my talent to furthering CGI's mission to help clients succeed through outstanding quality, competence, and thought leadership. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

